if it has a use list.\n\n3. **Root Cause Analysis**:\n   - The `llvm::wouldInstructionBeTriviallyDead`
function assumes that all operands of the `llvm.lifetime.end` intrinsic have use lists.\n   - This
assumption is invalid for `poison` values, which do not have use lists.\n\n4. **Proposed Edit Points**:\n
- Modify the `llvm::wouldInstructionBeTriviallyDead` function to handle `poison` values explicitly.\n   -
Add a check for `hasUseList()` before attempting to iterate over the uses of an operand.\n\n### Edit
Points:\n\n1. **File**: `llvm/lib/Transforms/Utils/Local.cpp`\n   - **Lines**: 487-489\n   - **Change**:\n
